quran[58]{c,v,t}:
  37,145,"But We caused him to be cast forth on a desert shore, sick as he was"
  37,146,And caused a gourd plant to grow over him
  37,147,"And We sent him once again to (his people, numbering) a hundred thousand, rather they tended to increase"
  37,148,"And they believed in him (this time), and so, (sparing them,) We allowed them to enjoy life for a term allotted to them"
  37,149,"So ask them, (O Messenger,) whether your Lord has daughters while sons are allotted for them"
  37,150,Or that We created the angels female and they were witnesses
  37,151,"Beware, it is surely one of their fabrications that they say"
  37,152,"God has begotten.\" Most certainly they are liars"
  37,153,"He has (made gender-discrimination and so) chosen daughters in preference to sons, has He"
  37,154,What is the matter with you? How can you judge so
  37,155,Will you not still reflect and be mindful
  37,156,Or do you have a clear authority (of evidence)
  37,157,"If so, produce your book (which), if you are truthful in your claim, (must have come from God)"
  37,158,And they have concocted a kin-relationship between Him and the jinn (to excuse their worshipping the jinn); whereas the jinn know quite well that they (are created and sustained by God and) are bound to be arraigned (before Him for judgment)
  37,159,"All-Glorified is He, absolutely exalted above such as they attribute to Him"
  37,160,But God’s servants endowed with sincerity in faith and practicing the Religion do not do so
  37,161,For sure you and those that you worship
  37,162,Cannot cause any to deviate concerning God
  37,163,Except those who have willfully adopted the way to the Blazing Flame
  37,164,"(The angels whom they assert to be God’s daughters say): \"There is none among us but has his duty and position assigned"
  37,165,And surely we are those ranged in ranks (ever-expecting God’s commands)
  37,166,And most certainly we are the ones glorifying Him (declaring Him to be above having any defects and partners)
  37,167,They (the polytheists) surely used to say
  37,168,If only We had had a Reminder of the like those who lived before us had
  37,169,Then we would certainly have been God’s servants endowed with sincerity in faith and practicing the Religion
  37,170,Yet (now the Qur’an has come to them) they disbelieve in it; so they will come to know
  37,171,Indeed Our word (of promise) has already gone forth in respect of Our servants sent with Our Message (of guidance and warning)
  37,172,That they would surely be helped to victory
  37,173,"And that surely Our host (the host of the true believers), they are certainly the victors"
  37,174,"So turn aside from them for a little while, (do not care what they do and say)"
  37,175,"And watch them and see (to what end their denial will lead them), as they also will see it"
  37,176,Or do they seek to hasten on Our punishment (that it befall them immediately)
  37,177,"But when it descends encompassing them, then evil will be the morning of those who have been warned"
  37,178,And ignore what they say and do for a little while
  37,179,"And watch them and see (what the ultimate end of all people will be), as they also will see it"
  37,180,"All-Glorified is your Lord, the Lord of might and glory, exalted above all that they attribute (to Him)"
  37,181,And peace be upon the Messengers
  37,182,"And all praise and gratitude are for God, the Lord of the worlds"
  38,1,"Sad. (I swear) by the glorious Qur’an bearing the Reminder (with guidance to the truth and warning, that you are one who has been sent to convey God’s Religion)"
  38,2,"However, those who disbelieve are lost in self-glory and opposition"
  38,3,We destroyed before them many generations (who likewise willfully persisted in unbelief and opposition). (In the end) they called out for help but only when it was too late for the punishment (they had earned) to be canceled
  38,4,"They deem it strange that a warner from among them has come to them, and the unbelievers say: \"This man is but a sorcerer, a fraud (who makes fabrications in attribution to God)"
  38,5,"What! has he made all the deities into One God. This is a very strange thing, indeed"
  38,6,"The leaders among them went about inciting one another: \"Move on, and remain constant to your deities. Surely that (to which this man calls) is the very thing that is certainly intended (deliberately plotted by him and those who follow him)"
  38,7,We have not heard of this in recent ways of faith. This is surely nothing but a concoction
  38,8,"From among all of us has the Reminder been sent down on him?\" No! Rather, (on account of their self-glory) they are lost in doubts concerning My Reminder. No indeed! they have not yet tasted My punishment (so that they might abandon their arrogance and recognize the truth)"
  38,9,"Or do they own and control the treasures of the Mercy of your Lord, the All-Glorious with irresistible might, the All-Bestowing, (that they presume to object to your being chosen as the Messenger)"
  38,10,Or do they own the sovereignty of the heavens and the earth and all that is between them? Then let them ascend to the heavens by ropes (and see if they can prevent the Message from being sent to you)
  38,11,They are no more than a routed band of (disunited) parties there (awaiting a defeat as certain as the defeat of the hordes of old times who rejected the Messengers and were utterly abased)
  38,12,"Before them the people of Noah denied (their Messenger), and the Ad, and the Pharaoh with formidable strongholds"
  38,13,"And also the Thamud, and the people of Lot, and the people al-Aykah. Those are the hordes (of old times)"
  38,14,"Not one of them but denied the Messengers (sent to them), and therefore My retribution was their just, inevitable due"
  38,15,"These wait but for a single blast, which will tolerate no delay (to give them respite)"
  38,16,"Yet, they say: \"Our Lord! Hasten on to us our share before the Day of Reckoning"
  38,17,"Bear patiently all that they say, and remember Our servant David, powerful (in his glorification of God, in knowledge, in kingdom, and in fighting). Surely he was one ever turning to God in penitence"
  38,18,We subdued the mountains to glorify (their Lord) along with him in the afternoon and bright morning
  38,19,And the birds assembled; all were turned to Him (in devotion and glorification)
  38,20,"We strengthened his kingdom, and granted him wisdom and decisive speech (to inform, and convince, and lead)"